domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| education           = \n| alma_mater          = [[Nelson Mandela University]]\n| occupation          = Member of Parliament\n| profession          = Politician\n| known_for           = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| awards              =  \n| website             = \n}}\n'''Vuyolwethu Zungula''' (born 28 August 1987) is a South African politician who is the president of the [[African Transformation Movement]] (ATM). He and [[Thandiswa Marawu]] have representing the ATM in the [[National Assembly of South Africa]] since 22 May 2019. Zungula was born in [[Mthatha]] and has a degree from [[Nelson Mandela University]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Khumalo |first1=Juniour |title=It\u2019s about ideology, rather than biology for ATM\u2019s 31-year-old leader |url=https://city-press.news24.com/News/its-about-ideology-rather-than-biology-for-atms-31-year-old-leader-20190422 |accessdate=8 April 2020 |newspaper=City Press - News24 |date=22 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=ATM announces parliamentary, provincial legislature candidates |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/politics/atm-announces-parliamentary-provincial-legislature-candidates-23285517 |accessdate=8 April 2020 |newspaper=IOL |date=15 May 2019 |location=Port Elizabeth}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[https://www.pa.org.za/person/vuyolwethu-zungula/ Vuyolwethu Zungula \u2013 People's Assembly]\n*[https://www.parliament.gov.za/person-details/393 Mr Vuyolwethu Zungula \u2013 Parliament of South Africa]\n{{Current MPs of South Africa}}\n{{SouthAfrica-politician-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zungula, Vuyolwethu}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of South Africa]]\n[[Category:People from the Eastern Cape]]\n[[Category:Politicians of South Africa]]\n", "name_user": "Lefcentreright", "label": "safe", "